flowRoot.flowPara: Yarnball is an online database service and visual editor that operates entirely on the basis of nodes and links. There are no core data-types like numbers, booleans or strings. Instead, all data types, and any kind of structure, can be constructed from these building blocks.

A surface is an infinite plane on which nodes can be placed, and links drawn between them. Various other widgets and functions built-in to the surface allow a web to be constructed, queried and manipulated.
